summary: An Ordinance accepting a deed, executed on the 30th day of August, A. D., 1904, by the Northwestern Improvement Company, by its President, Howard Elliott, to the City of Seattle, for a part of the South 1/2 of Section 21; the West 1/2 of the N. E. 1/4 of the N. W. 1/4, the S. E. 1/4 of the N. E. 1/4 of the N. W. 1/4, the West 1/2 of the N. W. 1/4, and the S. E. 1/4 of the N. W. 1/4 of Section 23, and part of the S. W. 1/4 of the N. E. 1/4 of Section 23, all in Township 22, Range 7 East, less certain right-of-ways and easements, and subject to certain mining and timber rights as stipulated in said deed.
